WEBVTT

00:00:01.624 --> 00:00:03.120
A cold is an infection in

00:00:03.120 --> 00:00:05.008
the upper respiratory tract.

00:00:05.192 --> 00:00:07.552
Colds are caused by viruses.

00:00:07.696 --> 00:00:09.320
People spread the virus through

00:00:09.320 --> 00:00:11.944
sneezing, coughing, close contact,

00:00:11.940 --> 00:00:13.096
or touching objects

00:00:13.090 --> 00:00:14.784
someone else then handles.

00:00:15.160 --> 00:00:16.336
Symptoms of a cold

00:00:16.330 --> 00:00:18.160
usually last a week or 2.

00:00:18.160 --> 00:00:20.160
They include: coughing,

00:00:20.160 --> 00:00:21.864
scratchy or sore throat,

00:00:21.860 --> 00:00:23.832
runny or stuffy nose,

00:00:23.830 --> 00:00:25.024
sneezing,

00:00:25.020 --> 00:00:26.368
watery eyes,

00:00:26.360 --> 00:00:27.784
ear congestion,

00:00:27.780 --> 00:00:29.088
mild fever,

00:00:29.080 --> 00:00:30.072
headache.

00:00:30.648 --> 00:00:31.760
A cold cannot be

00:00:31.760 --> 00:00:33.096
cured with medicines.

00:00:33.288 --> 00:00:34.672
You can reduce your chances of

00:00:34.670 --> 00:00:36.480
getting a cold by avoiding contact

00:00:36.480 --> 00:00:38.088
with someone who has a cold

00:00:38.080 --> 00:00:39.752
and frequent hand washing,

00:00:39.750 --> 00:00:41.416
especially before touching your

00:00:41.410 --> 00:00:43.488
eyes, nose, or mouth.

